subSubSection.paragraph:
Adult habitus.
General color brown. Head with dark brown quadrangular spot covering ocellar triangle; paler laterally, anterior to M-line and on occiput (
Fig. 28
). Basal antennal segment pale brown, second and subsequent segments dark brown. Pronotum dark brown with scattered obscure pale rugosities. Legs brown to pale brown with narrow dark marking on apex of femora (
Fig. 32
). Cerci pale.
